notesStmt.note: Title from caption title (f. 1r); title on spine: Histor. del Nores.

msContents.summary: History composed in 1644, in four books, copied by Lorenzo di Agostini in 1688.

msItem.title: Della guerra fra Filippo II, re di Spagna, e Papa Paolo Quarto
msItem.author: De Nores, Pietro
msItem.colophon: Colophon: Scritta da Pietro di Nores in Roma à 12 di aprile...1644 e copiato da me Lorenzo di Agostini à 24 aprile 1688 (f. 179r).

supportDesc.extent: 210 leaves : 264 x 193 (215 x 145) mm. bound to 273 x 203 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 210; [ix], [1-201]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by several hands.

binding.p: Contemporary half leather. Spine brittle, with lower section detached. Moderate ink oxidation and some worm damage.

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Henry C. Lea, 1888 (bookplate, inside upper cover; signature and date, f. i recto).
Bequeathed to the University of Pennsylvania as part of the library of Henry C. Lea, 1909.
